<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>On Tuesday, Joyce walked uphill to the gate of Mama Winnie’s home.She was dressed in black, wore a doek and a shawl which had Madikizela-Mandela’s face on it.She was accompanied by an entourage of ANC Women's League members, who were also dressed in black.Addressing the media, “To the South African nation they must not listen to the hearsay and create their own news about something that is non-existent.”“As Stopmie Seipei’s mother, I came here to offer condolences to the family of Winnie as she was the mother of the nation.“As the member of the women’s league, I don’t have anything against Mama Winnie.”She said after meeting the family, she was very happy. “The person I first met here is Zinzi, I’m very happy.”ANC Secretary General, Ace Magashule told the media that Joyce wanted to come here and pass her condolences.“We said we will create that space for her and the family was very happy, and she did pass her condolences to the family and that was it.”He said he was not sure that she will be coming to the funeral, but whatever her decision may be, the ANC branches will assist her.